<item>
            <title>[LU-11541] DKMS building the lustre client modules with Mellanox OFED is broken on Debian/Ubuntu</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11541</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Commit&#160;baf83c76f11a28a105e92e59b178a7ca2fb66156 has broken dkms builds with Mellanox OFED based builds on Debian/Ubuntu.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;config/lustre-build-linux.m4 need to retain the LB_USES_DPKG block so that&#160;uses_dpkg remains defined since it is being used in&#160;lnet/autoconf/lustre-lnet.m4 to detect how to handle the ofed_info output. And&#160;config/lustre-build.m4 should then also be reverted regarding the above commit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is also another problem when using Mellanox OFED 4.4 DKMS built kernel modules.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/usr/src/ofa_kernel/default doesn&apos;t exist in the&#160;mlnx-ofed-kernel-dkms package, it is only created (as a link) during package installation. Therefore the&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;O2IBPATHS=$(eval $OFED_INFO | egrep -w &apos;mlnx-ofed-kernel-dkms|mlnx-ofa_kernel-devel|compat-rdma-devel|kernel-ib-devel|ofa_kernel-devel&apos; | xargs $LSPKG | grep &apos;&amp;#40;/openib&amp;#124;/ofa_kernel/default&amp;#41;$&apos; | head -n1)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in lnet/autoconf/lustre-lnet.m4 fails.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached patch fixes the problem (assuming the&#160;LB_USES_DPKG block has been put back)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
